abstract: >-
  TurboGEPA is a high-performance fork of the GEPA (Genetic-Pareto)
  framework designed for maximum speed of prompt evolution. It extends
  GEPA's core algorithm with island-based parallelism, async orchestration,
  ASHA successive halving, disk caching, and adaptive configuration to
  achieve 3-10x speedups over the original implementation. TurboGEPA
  preserves GEPA's core innovation of LLM-based reflective mutation with
  Pareto selection while focusing on performance engineering for
  production deployments.
